@mikepenz Found out what is the problem, it is not onProfileChanged() return value that is causing the drawer to close. It is the setSelectionAtPosition() behaviour that has changed from 4.6.4 to 5.0.7. Previously in 4.6.4, calling this method will not cause the drawer to close
```
public boolean onProfileChanged(View view, IProfile profile, boolean current) {
// simulate a LoaderManager callback 1 second later whenever a profile is changed to load new list of PrimaryDrawerItem
handler.postDelayed(new Runnable() {

    @Override
    public void run() {

        drawer.addItem(new PrimaryDrawerItem().withName("drawer item " + ++autoIncrement));

        /**
         * this is the method call that causing the drawer to close. In 4.6.4, it doesn't do that
         */
        drawer.setSelectionAtPosition(1);
    }
}, 1000);

return true;

}
```
